The paper focuses on the impact of class imbalance on classification performance of convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which is a common problem in computer vision (CV) tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV. The paper also compares several methods to address the issue, which involves machine learning techniques such as oversampling and undersampling, indicating that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper uses deep learning techniques, specifically CNNs, which suggests it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.DL (Deep Learning).
